88
00:07:34,709 --> 00:07:36,409
(Lee Tae Kyung)

89
00:07:38,609 --> 00:07:39,779
Hey, Tae Kyung.

90
00:08:23,689 --> 00:08:25,359
You're fearless.

91
00:08:26,229 --> 00:08:27,498
You haven't changed.

92
00:08:28,099 --> 00:08:30,059
Aren't you scared to come here alone so late at night?

93
00:08:30,059 --> 00:08:31,298
Even the light was off.

94
00:08:32,199 --> 00:08:33,268
I'm not.

95
00:08:33,868 --> 00:08:36,538
I wish her ghost would appear and tell me...

96
00:08:36,668 --> 00:08:38,439
what happened that night.

97
00:08:39,638 --> 00:08:42,878
I chose the right person to hand this case over to.

98
00:08:44,309 --> 00:08:47,979
Oh, right. You asked me for the delivery man's call log.

99
00:08:48,748 --> 00:08:50,589
Did he call the victim?

100
00:08:51,918 --> 00:08:55,158
During the accident, his phone was destroyed.

101
00:08:55,158 --> 00:08:56,989
It wasn't in the list of lost articles either.

102
00:08:56,989 --> 00:08:58,089
It's been way too long, so the telecommunication company...

103
00:08:58,089 --> 00:09:00,128
doesn't have any records left either.

104
00:09:01,059 --> 00:09:02,829
His number wasn't canceled though.

105
00:09:03,258 --> 00:09:05,368
The phone was re-registered under his older brother's name.

106
00:09:06,628 --> 00:09:08,138
His older brother?

107
00:09:08,199 --> 00:09:12,069
They couldn't keep the number under a deceased's name.

108
00:09:16,209 --> 00:09:19,079
I looked through the past two years' worth of call logs.

109
00:09:20,079 --> 00:09:21,579
But it was never used.

110
00:09:24,349 --> 00:09:26,788
We couldn't find the victim's phone either, right?

111
00:09:26,788 --> 00:09:28,288
The culprit probably took it.

112
00:09:28,459 --> 00:09:31,788
And her number was canceled a few hours after the murder.

113
00:09:32,829 --> 00:09:34,929
I'm sure there was some crucial information in it.

114
00:09:38,929 --> 00:09:41,038
The delivery man came to the crime scene...

115
00:09:41,538 --> 00:09:43,199
and got into an accident the day after.

116
00:09:50,778 --> 00:09:52,109
You ran out of side dishes, right?

117
00:09:52,979 --> 00:09:54,248
Goodness.

118
00:09:54,648 --> 00:09:57,849
You've been giving me food for the past several years.

119
00:09:57,849 --> 00:09:59,788
I ought to do it until the day I die.

120
00:09:59,949 --> 00:10:03,018
You were my mentor when I first joined this line of work.

121
00:10:06,788 --> 00:10:08,758
I heard your wife's ill.

122
00:10:09,359 --> 00:10:11,268
Make sure you eat well.

123
00:10:12,229 --> 00:10:15,398
All right. Thank you for the food.

124
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:32,719
What do you mean?

125
00:10:37,329 --> 00:10:39,258
Yang Chul Ki seems suspicious.

126
00:10:41,998 --> 00:10:43,128
Yang Chul Ki?

127
00:10:43,459 --> 00:10:47,839
My brother had visited the crime scene seven years ago...

128
00:10:47,839 --> 00:10:49,199
when Chul Ki committed the murder.

129
00:10:50,739 --> 00:10:52,609
And the day after, my brother got into an accident.

130
00:10:53,538 --> 00:10:55,579
Are you saying he's related to your brother's accident?

131
00:10:57,248 --> 00:10:58,908
But it doesn't make any sense.

132
00:10:58,908 --> 00:11:01,449
My brother died in a DUI incident.

133
00:11:03,148 --> 00:11:04,719
And those scumbags who caused the accident were...

134
00:11:07,189 --> 00:11:08,189
Remember?

135
00:11:16,859 --> 00:11:18,028
It's a coincidence.

136
00:11:18,768 --> 00:11:19,929
That can't be.

137
00:11:20,599 --> 00:11:21,599
You're probably right.

138
00:11:23,099 --> 00:11:24,109
But...

139
00:11:26,239 --> 00:11:27,309
he smiled.

140
00:11:27,878 --> 00:11:28,878
That jerk smiled.

141
00:11:30,008 --> 00:11:31,548
I saw it clearly.

142
00:11:31,949 --> 00:11:33,819
You met this delivery man...

143
00:11:34,079 --> 00:11:35,248
on the day of her murder.

144
00:11:37,888 --> 00:11:40,118
For some reason, it's been bothering me.

145
00:11:40,118 --> 00:11:43,059
I will look into Yang Chul Ki.

146
00:11:43,059 --> 00:11:45,459
No. I will look into him myself.

147
00:11:47,658 --> 00:11:48,658
I'll get going.

148
00:11:50,229 --> 00:11:51,668
What will that change?

149
00:11:56,969 --> 00:11:58,439
Even if you find out more about this,

150
00:12:00,309 --> 00:12:02,038
our decision won't be...

151
00:12:06,248 --> 00:12:07,778
Right. It's probably a coincidence.

152
00:12:08,118 --> 00:12:09,219
Forget about it.

153
00:12:13,689 --> 00:12:14,689
But Woo Yong,

154
00:12:17,758 --> 00:12:20,258
why are you trying to get Yang Chul Ki out?

155
00:12:28,168 --> 00:12:29,798
Forget I asked. I'm leaving.

156
00:13:07,908 --> 00:13:09,479
Even if you find out more about this,

157
00:13:10,109 --> 00:13:11,849
our decision won't be...

158
00:13:12,609 --> 00:13:14,079
What will that change?

159
00:13:17,418 --> 00:13:18,949
Report this.

160
00:13:19,689 --> 00:13:20,959
Jerk.

161
00:13:21,189 --> 00:13:24,128
Darn it. Is this your first time seeing someone die?

162
00:13:25,829 --> 00:13:27,859
Do a better job filming this.

163
00:13:42,209 --> 00:13:44,849
(You've passed the final round of the 53rd Bar Exam.)

164
00:14:53,778 --> 00:14:55,418
Are you planning to kill them?

165
00:15:02,288 --> 00:15:04,788
At times like this, there are only two options.

166
00:15:05,888 --> 00:15:07,189
Either you forgive them...

167
00:15:07,699 --> 00:15:09,128
or get back at them.

168
00:15:11,298 --> 00:15:12,298
Who are you?

169
00:15:12,829 --> 00:15:15,038
After you kill them, are you planning...

170
00:15:16,368 --> 00:15:18,439
to end your life as well?

171
00:15:29,349 --> 00:15:30,989
What choice do I have?

172
00:15:33,319 --> 00:15:35,288
I've tried everything I could, but it's not working.

173
00:15:35,689 --> 00:15:37,729
My little brother faced a wrongful death.

174
00:15:38,128 --> 00:15:39,729
But the law is a load of trash, and those jerks...

175
00:15:39,729 --> 00:15:41,758
aren't sorry for what they've done to my brother at all.

176
00:15:42,459 --> 00:15:44,028
What else could I do now?

177
00:15:45,199 --> 00:15:46,729
Do exactly what they did to you.

178
00:15:48,469 --> 00:15:49,668
However, you should do that...

179
00:15:50,498 --> 00:15:53,038
without hurting yourself.

180
00:15:53,038 --> 00:15:54,038
That's how you...

181
00:15:55,378 --> 00:15:56,878
take your revenge.

182
00:16:04,018 --> 00:16:05,148
I've been wondering...

183
00:16:06,349 --> 00:16:08,258
if I could help you out...

184
00:16:12,329 --> 00:16:13,528
as long as...

185
00:16:14,559 --> 00:16:16,128
you can give me what I want.

186
00:17:07,518 --> 00:17:15,159
