190
00:18:23,788 --> 00:18:24,929
Oh, right. Detective Kang.

191
00:18:48,219 --> 00:18:49,219
Hey!

192
00:18:49,548 --> 00:18:50,619
My partner!

193
00:18:50,719 --> 00:18:52,018
Goodness.

194
00:18:52,588 --> 00:18:53,788
If you're drunk,

195
00:18:53,788 --> 00:18:55,758
just go home like a good boy.

196
00:18:56,358 --> 00:18:57,518
Have you gone mad?

197
00:18:57,929 --> 00:18:59,758
Do you know how much the cab would cost to Ilsan?

198
00:19:00,429 --> 00:19:03,498
Were you looking into the unsolved case again before you left?

199
00:19:04,298 --> 00:19:06,828
Come on. That case is so obvious.

200
00:19:06,998 --> 00:19:08,338
Why do you think a pretty girl got murdered?

201
00:19:08,338 --> 00:19:10,239
I'm 100 percent sure it was a crime of passion.

202
00:19:10,699 --> 00:19:11,808
Detective Ma.

203
00:19:12,308 --> 00:19:15,179
There are no obvious cases in the world.

204
00:19:15,179 --> 00:19:17,778
There are only detectives who can't see beyond the obvious.

205
00:19:20,808 --> 00:19:22,848
Let me give you a piece of advice since you're my partner.

206
00:19:23,479 --> 00:19:25,949
Try to spend your last days at the station quietly.

207
00:19:26,788 --> 00:19:28,258
When you're about to retire, you have to watch out...

208
00:19:28,258 --> 00:19:30,119
- even for the falling leaves. - Come on.

209
00:19:30,659 --> 00:19:33,088
- You're the one to talk. - Darn it.

210
00:19:33,088 --> 00:19:34,899
Cut down on drinking.

211
00:19:35,129 --> 00:19:36,459
- Gosh. - You're pretty decent...

212
00:19:36,459 --> 00:19:37,869
when you're sober.

213
00:19:40,768 --> 00:19:42,838
Come on. Get a new car.

214
00:19:43,338 --> 00:19:45,639
No one drives a car that ran 380,000km.

215
00:19:45,639 --> 00:19:47,008
It's working fine.

216
00:19:47,008 --> 00:19:48,479
It's better than you, actually.

217
00:19:49,308 --> 00:19:52,808
Hey, do me a favor. Stop causing trouble.

218
00:19:54,318 --> 00:19:56,078
Darn it. Come on.

219
00:19:56,848 --> 00:19:58,548
Go, go. Go then.

220
00:21:20,669 --> 00:21:23,998
- What happened? - He only worked all the time.

221
00:21:24,439 --> 00:21:26,709
- There he is. - He's coming.

222
00:21:26,808 --> 00:21:28,139
Get back to work.

223
00:21:32,748 --> 00:21:35,278
What? Did something happen?

224
00:21:40,048 --> 00:21:42,219
- Mr. Guk, about Detective Kang's... - Prosecutor Seo.

225
00:21:47,028 --> 00:21:49,058
Yes, go ahead.

226
00:21:50,858 --> 00:21:52,028
Oh, well...

227
00:21:58,439 --> 00:22:00,709
- Bring it in a little more. - Yes.

228
00:22:17,318 --> 00:22:18,729
Hey, who's that?

229
00:22:19,159 --> 00:22:20,429
Hold him down!

230
00:22:20,629 --> 00:22:22,328
Hey, get him! Stop him!

231
00:22:24,058 --> 00:22:25,629
- Goodness. - Let go of me!

232
00:22:25,629 --> 00:22:26,869
Let go, you jerks!

233
00:22:27,268 --> 00:22:29,038
I'm his partner, you jerks!

234
00:22:29,038 --> 00:22:30,498
Move, you jerks!

235
00:22:30,498 --> 00:22:31,709
Let him go.

236
00:22:32,768 --> 00:22:34,209
He was his partner.

237
00:23:17,649 --> 00:23:19,788
Prosecution. We're with the prosecution.

238
00:23:28,399 --> 00:23:29,699
What happened?

239
00:23:29,858 --> 00:23:31,699
The car was pretty old.

240
00:23:31,699 --> 00:23:34,429
There was no light in the night, so he hit the rail by accident...

241
00:23:34,429 --> 00:23:37,169
Stop talking nonsense. We said goodbye in Seoul yesterday.

242
00:23:37,498 --> 00:23:38,939
Are you saying he came here all night long?

243
00:23:39,939 --> 00:23:42,038
That he hit the rail and killed himself?

244
00:23:42,139 --> 00:23:45,209
I'm telling you. The car is really old.

245
00:23:46,149 --> 00:23:47,449
Do you know who he is?

246
00:23:48,219 --> 00:23:50,048
Do you know how many criminals he put behind bars?

247
00:23:52,149 --> 00:23:53,288
Do the investigation right.

248
00:24:13,308 --> 00:24:15,608
Okay. Thanks. Yes.

249
00:24:16,679 --> 00:24:18,048
I'm going to the prosecutors' office.

250
00:24:18,048 --> 00:24:20,008
Do you want a ride?

251
00:24:20,108 --> 00:24:22,248
It's right around the corner. I'll walk as my workout.

252
00:24:22,379 --> 00:24:23,518
Oh, wait.

253
00:24:24,248 --> 00:24:26,788
It looks like something happened with Prosecutor Seo's side.

254
00:24:27,518 --> 00:24:29,189
The detective who investigated...

255
00:24:29,189 --> 00:24:31,959
Yang Chul Ki's case seven years ago with her...

256
00:24:31,959 --> 00:24:34,429
suddenly died in an accident.

257
00:24:35,298 --> 00:24:36,929
Doesn't feel right, does it?

258
00:25:56,038 --> 00:25:57,179
You idiot.

259
00:26:00,149 --> 00:26:03,248
You're defending a guy who could have killed your brother.

260
00:26:07,518 --> 00:26:08,758
Idiot.

261
00:26:21,538 --> 00:26:23,268
They're making his funeral arrangements.

262
00:26:23,899 --> 00:26:25,838
His family is against getting an autopsy.

263
00:26:27,268 --> 00:26:29,608
The case will be closed as death by accident.

264
00:26:56,699 --> 00:26:57,869
(7 previous convictions, Yang Chul Ki)

265
00:26:57,869 --> 00:26:59,669
(32 years old at the time, 39 years old now)

266
00:26:59,669 --> 00:27:01,508
(Initial caller of the murder case, Choi Soo Jeong's manager)

267
00:27:27,469 --> 00:27:29,298
A detective died yesterday.

268
00:27:29,469 --> 00:27:31,768
He was reinvestigating the Ahyeon-dong Murder Case.

269
00:27:33,568 --> 00:27:35,078
What does that have to do with me?

270
00:27:36,479 --> 00:27:39,709
I'm like a sewer, aren't I? Throwing at me when things happen.

271
00:27:40,748 --> 00:27:41,778
Prosecutor Seo.

272
00:27:42,748 --> 00:27:44,048
I was in prison.

273
00:27:46,048 --> 00:27:47,449
You told them to do it.

274
00:27:48,588 --> 00:27:49,788
What are you talking about?

275
00:27:50,858 --> 00:27:53,528
There was a message from you on his phone.

276
00:27:54,159 --> 00:27:56,659
"If you continue to dig up the case from seven years ago,"

277
00:27:56,828 --> 00:27:58,528
"I'll hire someone to kill you."

278
00:28:02,739 --> 00:28:03,768
How does that make any sense?

279
00:28:03,768 --> 00:28:05,709
I'm going to make sure it makes sense starting now.

280
00:28:08,179 --> 00:28:09,439
You can fabricate the evidence...

281
00:28:09,439 --> 00:28:11,778
to be innocent after killing someone.

282
00:28:11,778 --> 00:28:14,608
It's a piece of cake to fabricate something on a phone.

283
00:28:18,248 --> 00:28:19,389
A prosecutor shouldn't do that.

284
00:28:20,788 --> 00:28:21,919
The security camera.

285
00:28:22,788 --> 00:28:23,858
Is there a security camera in here?

286
00:28:23,858 --> 00:28:25,088
There's nothing like that.

287
00:28:25,959 --> 00:28:27,058
Listen up.

288
00:28:27,489 --> 00:28:30,058
You will be indicted for instigating murder...

289
00:28:30,058 --> 00:28:31,358
of the detective who died yesterday.

290
00:28:31,358 --> 00:28:33,229
And I will throw in a charge for murder as the key suspect...

291
00:28:33,229 --> 00:28:34,629
of the Ahyeon-dong Murder Case.

292
00:28:34,629 --> 00:28:37,798
The evidence will include the threatening message you sent...

293
00:28:37,798 --> 00:28:40,409
along with a weapon that you used seven years ago,

294
00:28:40,808 --> 00:28:42,108
with your fingerprint all over it.

295
00:28:42,108 --> 00:28:43,379
What are you doing?

296
00:28:44,239 --> 00:28:45,248
Are you insane?

297
00:28:45,248 --> 00:28:47,709
I'll make sure it's not too obvious. Don't worry.

298
00:28:47,909 --> 00:28:49,748
I have enough experience as a prosecutor.

299
00:28:52,548 --> 00:28:54,149
You can take responsibility...

300
00:28:54,149 --> 00:28:56,889
for all of these cases just as you wished.

301
00:28:59,528 --> 00:29:00,758
Oh, on top of that,

302
00:29:02,098 --> 00:29:05,129
I will include all the wicked deeds that you have done, including...

303
00:29:05,129 --> 00:29:06,998
violence, fraud, threats, and everything else,

304
00:29:07,528 --> 00:29:09,939
so that you can rot in prison for life.
